# Arch Linux Documentation - OS_Wiki

System Name: Arch Linux
Kernel: Linux (Rolling release, latest kernel)
Based on: Nothing (independent)
Created by: Judd Vinet (initially for i686 arch)
Maintained by: Arch Linux Community
Initial release: 2002
Source model: Open source
License: GPL/0BSD
Architecture support: x86_64 (amd64) official support. Unofficial support with ARM and i686 (32-bit)
Package manager: Pacman (Binary), created by Judd Vinet
Desktop Environment: Any (CLI install)
System type: Desktop
Target audience: Advanced users, power users, rolling release enthusiasts and technology students.
Not recommended for: begginer people that use Windows or donÂ´t have experience with computers, those who want something ready-made and plug-and-play.
Official site: https://archlinux.org/
ISO size for download: 1,4 GB
Description: Independent Linux distribution, created initially by Judd Vinet. Installation is done manually using only the terminal (command line). 
It is recommended for users who want to build a system completely made by themselves and highly customizable. It follows the KISS and DIY philosophies, which stand for, respectively, Keep It Simple Stupid and Do It Yourself. 
Uses Pacman as a binary package manager. It doesn't have a default desktop environment, as the installation is done from scratch via terminal, so it's up to you to decide.
